findings.suggestion:
Add a test: configure routingOverrides to force classification to 'local' tier, but do not provide a local provider. Verify that the call falls back to the lightweight provider and succeeds. Example:

it('falls back to lightweight when override routes to local but local is absent', async () => {
  const lightweight = createTrackingProvider('lightweight')
  const standard = createTrackingProvider('standard')
  const router = new ModelRouter({
    providers: { lightweight, standard },
    routingOverrides: { classification: 'local' },
  })
  await router.generateStructured({ system: 'Classify this', prompt: 'x', schemaDescription: '{}' })
  expect(lightweight.calls).toHaveLength(1)
})

